title: Independent candidate Ahad Ali Shah wins NA-33 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate, Syed Shah Ahad Ali Shah has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-33, Nowshera-I by securing 93,492 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf Parliamentarian candidate, Pervez Khattak who bagged 26,574 votes.
The votersâ€™ turn-out remained 45.58%.
